# ShellCheck config for conduck-connect — public on purpose, so an auditor sees
# exactly what is suppressed and why.
#
# Nothing is suppressed. CI runs `shellcheck --severity=warning`, which the
# script passes with no `disable=` directives; the info-level SC2015
# ("A && B || C is not if-then-else") notes on a handful of intentional
# best-effort status lines fall below that threshold.
#
# If a suppression ever becomes necessary, name the symbol and the reason here
# rather than silencing a whole check — a reader of this file should be able to
# tell a deliberate exemption from an unnoticed bug.
